docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:33:| A-029 | `GET /api/v1/members/` initially accepts the narrow enum values needed by the source examples and S05 directory labels: `member_type` = `individual_farmer`/`fpc`/`producer_institution`, `membership_status` = `active`/`inactive`/`pending_verification`, `kyc_status` = `verified`/`missing`/`rekyc_due`/`pending`, and `default_status` = `no_default`/`existing_default`/`past_default`. Broader lifecycle/status vocabularies are deferred to their owning profile, KYC, active-member, and eligibility slices. | `api-contracts.md` §13.1 names the filters and shows representative values, while `screen-spec.md` S05 gives display labels but no canonical full enum table. The slice must validate filters without inventing eligibility/KYC/default business rules. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §13.1; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S05; `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.1; `docs/slices/004A-member-directory-api-and-ui.md` | 004A-member-directory-api-and-ui and future member/KYC status slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-07 | If source docs later define a richer member/KYC/default status catalogue, extend `sfpcl_credit/members/models.py`, `members/services.py`, API contract docs, and frontend filter options with matching tests. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:35:| A-031 | 004D treats legal majority for nominee validation as 18 years, calculated from `date_of_birth` on the server's current date at create time. | Source docs say nominees must not be minors and `api-contracts.md` §14.3 names `NOMINEE_MINOR_NOT_ALLOWED`, but they do not state the exact legal-majority age or jurisdiction-specific calculation date. Age 18 is the standard Indian legal-majority default and keeps the rule explicit without inventing a nominee-count or relationship policy. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §14.1-§14.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.4; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S08; `docs/slices/004D-nominee-validation-and-ui.md` | 004D-nominee-validation-and-ui and future nominee/application submission slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | If source docs later define a different nominee majority threshold or require age-at-application to use loan application submission date, update `members.services`, tests, and stored snapshot behavior. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:36:| A-032 | 004G gates land-holding and crop-plan lists with `members.member.read` and creates with `members.member.update`; no new land/crop permission codes are seeded. | `auth-permissions.md` §12.2 and the endpoint map define member, nominee, shareholding, and active-status permissions, but no land/crop-specific codes. The slice requires using the narrowest source-compatible existing member permission rather than inventing codes. | `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §12.2 and endpoint map; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §17.1-§17.2; `docs/slices/004G-landholding-and-crop-plan-records.md` | 004G-landholding-and-crop-plan-records and future land/crop permission hardening slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | If source docs add exact land/crop permissions, seed them and update `sfpcl_credit.members.services`, backend tests, frontend route/action checks, and this assumption. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:40:| A-036 | 005B submit enforces only the selected slice's persisted request facts: member, positive requested amount, declared purpose, and purpose category. Nominee and application-document placeholder gates from the broader source submit endpoint are deferred to the document/completeness slices. | `api-contracts.md` §19.5 lists broader gate conditions, but the selected 005B slice explicitly excludes completeness, document checklist verification, deficiencies, and nominee/document requirements unless the source pass puts them in 005B. Implementing them now would require models and business rules owned by later slices. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §19.5; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §20.1; `docs/source/screen-spec-member-portal.md` MP08; `docs/slices/005B-application-submit-and-status-transition.md` | 005B-application-submit-and-status-transition and future document/completeness slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Future document/completeness slices must add exact nominee and document placeholder validations before appraisal/completeness advancement. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:50:| A-046 | 006A returns `member_active_check = manual_evidence_required` when a member is active but no source-backed continuous produce/service history exists; it does not infer BR-004 through BR-007 from membership status alone. Existing verified `Member.active_member_status` facts can still produce `pass` or `relaxation`. | BR-004 through BR-007 require produce/service history or relaxation evidence, but current persistence has only member/profile summary fields and no source-backed history rows for continuous-year calculation. Inventing a supply-history calculation would create a business rule the source documents do not state. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` BR-004 through BR-007; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.1; `docs/working/digests/epic-006-eligibility-loan-limit-appraisal.md` | 006A-active-member-eligibility-service and future active-member/supply-history slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Add source-backed produce/service history models and replace this manual-evidence result when the active-member history slice is implemented. |
